Class variables. Every "instance" ("object") of this class

This is the "constructor." Every class should
have one. It always has the same name of
the class. The constructor is executed when
a new "instance" of the class is generated.
Thus, the constructor should set up values
for class variables. It is like the setup()
function we have used previously.
